	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I remember a colleague saying how much they liked the iMac's SD card slot (which is non spring-loaded). I didn't understand this at the time; I always liked spring-loaded slots.<br /><br />Now I know...<br /><br />Fast forward four years later: I bought a 3DS. Now fast forward one more year: I finally buy a non-digital game. The cartridge slot is spring-loaded, which doesn't seem to be a problem until I realize that I now have a game in the slot, or <strong>AT LEAST THERE SHOULD BE.</strong> <img src="./images/smilies/icon_evil.gif" alt=":evil:" title="Evil or Very Mad" /> Often when I pull my 3DS out of my pocket or backpack, the game is ejected. My brother even accidentally ejected his game while playing it. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /><br /><br />Is anyone else bothered by this design decision?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


